Simualation config of an XYZ machine with 3 machining heads.

Uses switchable custom kinematics to map the Z-axis to joint-(2,3,4) respectively.

Note: M128, M129 and M130 can be used to switch ini settings for the Z-axis 
depending on the active kinematic. 




To test:

Install the custom kinematic component on a RIP installation:

  halcompile --install <your-path>/xyz-multihead/xyz_multihead.comp 

Install the custom kinematic component on a DEB installation:

  sudo halcompile --install <your-path>/xyz-multihead/xyz_multihead.comp 



Note 'halcompile' requires the 'linuxcnc-dev' package to be installed.
